- line 9: `taxFor(13.5)` returns a number, `Number((...).toFixed(2))` → `1.35` ✓
- line 10: `totalFor` → `round(13.5) + round(1.35)` = `13.5 + 1.35`, which is exactly `14.85` as a double (both operands are clean 2-decimal doubles after rounding) ✓

Run `npm test` in `benchmarks/tasks/bigproject-baseline` to confirm — you should see `pricing.test.js: all assertions passed`. Note the fix repairs total computation going forward; any orders already stored with a concatenated `total` string would still hold the bad value (in this fixture the store is in-memory, so that's moot).
